00:07:43.338 --> 00:07:44.965
a little louder. but thank you.

239
00:07:45.006 --> 00:07:47.634
- Will you sign your
"Times" magazine cover?

240
00:07:47.717 --> 00:07:49.636
- [stammers]

241
00:07:49.719 --> 00:07:51.388
Yes. I--I've never--

242
00:07:51.471 --> 00:07:53.473
never signed anything
for anyone before.

243
00:07:53.556 --> 00:07:55.475
- [laughs]
- Wow. This is amazing.

244
00:07:55.517 --> 00:07:57.519
I really now understand why
parasocial relationships

245
00:07:57.602 --> 00:07:58.853
are replacing real ones.

246
00:07:58.937 --> 00:08:00.146
[laughs]

247
00:08:00.188 --> 00:08:01.523
- But seriously. thank you

248
00:08:01.606 --> 00:08:03.858
for all that you contribute
to society.

249
00:08:05.568 --> 00:08:07.070
- Anytime.

250
00:08:09.906 --> 00:08:11.783
- I'll catch you around.

251
00:08:11.866 --> 00:08:12.951
- Yeah. I'll be around all day.

252
00:08:13.034 --> 00:08:14.327
- Coolie.

253
00:08:14.369 --> 00:08:16.997
- Coolie. Coolie.

254
00:08:17.038 --> 00:08:18.999
- I can't tell you
how sorry I am.

255
00:08:19.040 --> 00:08:20.000
Please. It's on me.

256
00:08:20.083 --> 00:08:21.459
Thank you. Thanks.

257
00:08:21.543 --> 00:08:22.669
Thanks for coming.

258
00:08:22.711 --> 00:08:24.337
- Ticket.
- Oh. Ezekiel. [chuckles]

259
00:08:24.421 --> 00:08:25.839
How nice to see
a familiar face.

260
00:08:25.880 --> 00:08:27.215
What can I sign for you?

261
00:08:27.298 --> 00:08:29.342
- I've actually signed
something for you.

262
00:08:29.384 --> 00:08:31.219
It's my resignation letter
as president

263
00:08:31.302 --> 00:08:33.680
of the Deborah Vance Fan Club.
Southwest Branch.

264
00:08:33.763 --> 00:08:35.682
- But Ezekiel. you--
you've been a pillar

265
00:08:35.765 --> 00:08:37.684
of the Little Debbie community
for years!

266
00:08:37.767 --> 00:08:39.644
- I heard that Kathy Griffin
is looking for an infusion

267
00:08:39.686 --> 00:08:42.689
into her base. so I am taking
my talents elsewhere.

268
00:08:42.731 --> 00:08:45.233
- OK.
OK. what--what is going on?

269
00:08:45.316 --> 00:08:46.693
What is the problem?

270
00:08:46.776 --> 00:08:48.695
- The problem is
that you went Hollywood.

271
00:08:48.737 --> 00:08:51.823
- [gasps]
I did not go Hollywood!

272
00:08:51.906 --> 00:08:53.199
- Yes. you did.

273
00:08:53.283 --> 00:08:54.534
You haven't sent out
Deborah's Dos and Don'ts

274
00:08:54.617 --> 00:08:56.036
in almost two years.

275
00:08:56.119 --> 00:08:57.579
I don't know what to do
and what not to do.

276
00:08:57.662 --> 00:08:59.497
Sometimes I just
sit in the dark.

277
00:08:59.581 --> 00:09:00.874
- Yeah!
- Yeah!

278
00:09:00.915 --> 00:09:03.460
- You discontinued
your car insurance plan!

279
00:09:03.543 --> 00:09:05.378
And now I'm uninsured.
- Yeah!

280
00:09:05.420 --> 00:09:07.839
- Oh. honey.
you gotta have insurance.

281
00:09:07.881 --> 00:09:10.008
- And you discontinued the
Deborah Vance red light mask.

282
00:09:10.091 --> 00:09:12.385
I liked the burns!
It eventually turned to tan.

283
00:09:12.469 --> 00:09:13.553
- Yeah!
- Yeah!

284
00:09:13.595 --> 00:09:14.721
- You won't admit
you're a lizard!

285
00:09:14.804 --> 00:09:17.474
[crowd clamoring]

286
00:09:17.557 --> 00:09:19.684
- Hey. get into
a single-file line.

287
00:09:19.768 --> 00:09:21.061
or you will be tased!

288
00:09:21.102 --> 00:09:22.645
Do not fuck with me!

289
00:09:22.729 --> 00:09:25.190
[crowd murmuring]

290
00:09:25.273 --> 00:09:26.399
[clears throat]

291
00:09:26.483 --> 00:09:28.193
You should address
the lizard thing.

292
00:09:28.276 --> 00:09:29.861
It's gaining traction.

293
00:09:31.112 --> 00:09:32.739
Who's next?

294
00:09:32.781 --> 00:09:33.948
- And you really don't mind
switching with Deborah?

295
00:09:34.032 --> 00:09:35.116
- Oh. no. no. no. Not at all.

296
00:09:35.200 --> 00:09:37.118
That rant she did
against Lipka?

297
00:09:37.202 --> 00:09:39.079
Gold. legend.

298
00:09:39.120 --> 00:09:40.872
Guy's a freaking animal.
- Tell me about it.

299
00:09:40.955 --> 00:09:43.249
- Well. she always invites me
to her Fourth of July party.

300
00:09:43.333 --> 00:09:46.377
I never go.
but the invite's always nice.

301
00:09:46.461 --> 00:09:47.754
- Well. you're gonna be
on the list forever. man.

302
00:09:47.837 --> 00:09:49.089
We appreciate you.

303
00:09:49.130 --> 00:09:50.882
- Never too big. Jimmy.

304
00:09:50.965 --> 00:09:53.718
Never too big.
- My man. All right.

305
00:09:53.802 --> 00:09:56.262
OK. now that's a guy I could be
friends with--I love him.

306
00:09:56.346 --> 00:09:57.931
- Exactly what I like
to hear from you. boss.

307
00:09:58.014 --> 00:09:59.599
because I do not want
to see you fall prey

308
00:09:59.682 --> 00:10:01.601
to the male loneliness
epidemic.

309
00:10:01.643 --> 00:10:03.061
- No.
- I know. It's terrible.

310
00:10:03.144 --> 00:10:05.105
My Uncle Maury shot himself
in the head.

311
00:10:05.146 --> 00:10:06.773
- It's Renee O'Connor.

312
00:10:06.856 --> 00:10:08.066
- Who's that?

313
00:10:08.149 --> 00:10:09.192
- From "Xena:
Warrior Princess."

314
00:10:09.275 --> 00:10:10.860
the show--the show on The WB.

315
00:10:10.944 --> 00:10:12.278
- Oh. TV show.
- Yeah.

316
00:10:12.320 --> 00:10:13.780
- I haven't made it to TV yet.

317
00:10:13.822 --> 00:10:16.241
I'm still making it
through all the movies.

318
00:10:16.324 --> 00:10:18.201
- She's Xena?
- No. that's Gabrielle.

319
00:10:18.284 --> 00:10:20.537
That's Xena's battle partner.
her confidant.

320
00:10:20.620 --> 00:10:22.705
She's a traveling bard.
- Well. you gotta go say hi.

321
00:10:22.789 --> 00:10:24.207
- Hell. no.
I would be so nervous.

322
00:10:24.290 --> 00:10:25.875
I--I would faint.
No. I couldn't.

323
00:10:25.959 --> 00:10:27.544
I mean. I've seen every episode
multiple times.

324
00:10:27.627 --> 00:10:29.087
I even still have
a recurring dream

325
00:10:29.170 --> 00:10:30.964
that I'm helping Xena
save Prometheus

326
00:10:31.005 --> 00:10:32.674
so that humans don't lose their
capacity for healing and fire.

327
00:10:32.757 --> 00:10:34.342
- Jimmy. you're meeting her.

328
00:10:34.425 --> 00:10:35.760
You'll regret it if you don't.
Come on.

329
00:10:35.844 --> 00:10:37.762
- You think?
- I know so.

330
00:10:37.804 --> 00:10:39.097
- OK. OK.

331
00:10:39.180 --> 00:10:40.265
God. I wish I had
a beta blocker.

332
00:10:40.348 --> 00:10:41.307
- Ah.
- All right. let's go.

333
00:10:41.391 --> 00:10:43.184
- [chuckles] Whoo!

334
00:10:43.268 --> 00:10:44.602
- So are you working
on anything else.

335
00:10:44.686 --> 00:10:46.354
other than writing for Deborah?

336
00:10:46.437 --> 00:10:47.814
- Yeah. yeah. I actually
just wrote a movie

337
00:10:47.897 --> 00:10:49.607
about a girl who lives
at the mall. so--

338
00:10:49.691 --> 00:10:51.609
- Oh! Such a good idea.

339
00:10:51.693 --> 00:10:53.653
Got my tickets.
I am "saur" sat.

340
00:10:53.736 --> 00:10:55.530
- [laughs] You are so sweet.

341
00:10:55.613 --> 00:10:57.782
- Shit. wait.
this is just occurring to me.

342
00:10:57.866 --> 00:10:59.492
Are you gonna have
to leave Deborah?

343
00:10:59.576 --> 00:11:01.286
- No. no. I mean.

344
00:11:01.327 --> 00:11:02.745
especially not after
what she did for me

345
00:11:02.829 --> 00:11:04.205
at "Late Night."
- Mm.

346
00:11:05.582 --> 00:11:09.836
So what's your. like. dream?

347
00:11:09.919 --> 00:11:11.504
- You know. I've always wanted
to create my own show.

348
00:11:11.546 --> 00:11:12.839
- Oh.

349
00:11:12.881 --> 00:11:14.757
- I was voted
Most Likely to Showrun

350
00:11:14.841 --> 00:11:16.342
in my high school yearbook.

351
00:11:16.384 --> 00:11:18.928
I mean. I did create
the superlative. but still.

352
00:11:19.012 --> 00:11:20.930
- I really hope this isn't
weird that I know this.

353
00:11:21.014 --> 00:11:23.433
but. um. it's your
birthday today. right?

354
00:11:23.516 --> 00:11:25.643
- [laughs] Yeah. Yes. it is.

355
00:11:25.727 --> 00:11:28.021
- And you're turning 30. right?

356
00:11:28.104 --> 00:11:29.480
- Yeah.
- Poof!

357
00:11:29.564 --> 00:11:31.524
Pretty big milestone.
[chuckles]

358
00:11:31.608 --> 00:11:33.109
Are you. like.
freaking out about

359
00:11:33.193 --> 00:11:34.235
where you're at in your life?

360
00:11:34.319 --> 00:11:35.904
- No. not--I mean. no.

361
00:11:35.987 --> 00:11:37.363
not really. I don't think.

362
00:11:37.447 --> 00:11:39.365
Should I? No. No! I'm not.

363
00:11:39.407 --> 00:11:42.744
- Well. I'd love to get you
something for your birthday.

364
00:11:42.827 --> 00:11:44.037
like a cupcake or--

365
00:11:44.078 --> 00:11:45.914
- You don't have to.

366
00:11:45.997 --> 00:11:48.208
But if they have chocolate
cake. I'd take chocolate icing.

367
00:11:48.249 --> 00:11:49.876
Or if they have vanilla cake.

368
00:11:49.918 --> 00:11:51.711
I still would want
chocolate icing.

369
00:11:51.753 --> 00:11:53.087
But if Funfetti is in the mix.
of course--

370
00:11:53.171 --> 00:11:54.505
- They just have corn muffins.

371
00:11:54.589 --> 00:11:56.174
- Perfect.

372
00:11:56.257 --> 00:11:58.551
- It's your day.
- Whoo!

373
00:11:58.635 --> 00:12:00.386
- Why are you performing
only at Madison Square Garden

374
00:12:00.470 --> 00:12:01.763
and not Portsmouth.
New Hampshire?

375
00:12:01.846 --> 00:12:03.181
I mean. we are important too.

376
00:12:03.264 --> 00:12:05.058
We built
the Revolutionary War fleet.

377
00:12:05.141 --> 00:12:07.227
- And we so appreciate that.

378
00:12:07.310 --> 00:12:09.562
- You stopped doing your annual
Christmas conference call.

379
00:12:09.646 --> 00:12:11.814
Now. how we supposed
to sync up on micro-theme?

380
00:12:11.898 --> 00:12:14.317
- You never published
another book of Debokus.

381
00:12:14.400 --> 00:12:17.153
and the regular sudokus
are just too hard.

382
00:12:17.237 --> 00:12:18.529
- I'm mad you left QVC.

383
00:12:18.613 --> 00:12:20.573
- And I'm mad you didn't
leave QVC earlier.

384
00:12:20.615 --> 00:12:21.908
<i>[percussive music]</i>

385
00:12:21.950 --> 00:12:22.909
- Work it out.

386
00:12:22.951 --> 00:12:24.369
- I miss Marcus.

387
00:12:24.452 --> 00:12:26.579
Damien never sends us
locks of your hair.

388
00:12:26.663 --> 00:12:28.748
<i>ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ</i>

389
00:12:28.790 --> 00:12:30.250
- You didn't endorse
a candidate

390
00:12:30.291 --> 00:12:33.211
in the presidential election.
so I didn't vote.

391
00:12:33.294 --> 00:12:34.879
And now my kids
won't talk to me.

392
00:12:34.963 --> 00:12:36.464
- I sent you two
suspicious packages

393
00:12:36.547 --> 00:12:39.092
and didn't even receive
a cease-and-desist letter.

394
00:12:39.133 --> 00:12:40.093
You used to care.

395
00:12:40.176 --> 00:12:41.094
- OK. that's it!

396
00:12:41.177 --> 00:12:42.095
I need a break.

397
00:12:42.178 --> 00:12:43.304
- 10-minute break.

398
00:12:43.388 --> 00:12:45.723
[crowd groaning]

399
00:12:45.807 --> 00:12:48.101
- These people are
impossible to please.

400
00:12:48.184 --> 00:12:49.560
I mean. my fans seem
to think I owe them

401
00:12:49.644 --> 00:12:51.271
every single moment of my life.

402
00:12:51.312 --> 00:12:52.563
- Think of it this way.

403
00:12:52.647 --> 00:12:54.440
Today. you are being paid
to be yelled at.

404
00:12:54.482 --> 00:12:56.442
For some people. that's a kink.

405
00:12:56.526 --> 00:12:59.279
- [groaning]

406
00:12:59.320 --> 00:13:00.822
- Oh. yeah.
This is classic Gabby. yeah.

407
00:13:00.905 --> 00:13:03.283
- Oh. she looks the exact same.

408
00:13:03.366 --> 00:13:04.742
Did you know it was
actually the fans

409
00:13:04.826 --> 00:13:06.786
that saw Xena as a guest
character on "Hercules."

410
00:13:06.828 --> 00:13:08.454
and they were so enthusiastic

411
00:13:08.496 --> 00:13:10.248
that they actually helped get
the spin-off series made?

412
00:13:10.331 --> 00:13:12.917
- Grassroots movements are
always so inspiring.

413
00:13:13.001 --> 00:13:15.378
That is.
until they turn bloodthirsty.

414
00:13:15.461 --> 00:13:16.713
- Next!
- It's us.

415
00:13:16.796 --> 00:13:18.589
- Here we go. Here we go.
- We paid.

416
00:13:18.673 --> 00:13:20.216
- Hi. I'm Renee.
- Oh. I'm Renee--

417
00:13:20.300 --> 00:13:21.467
um. you're Renee.
- Yeah. I'm Renee.

418
00:13:21.551 --> 00:13:22.635
- You're Renee.
- I am Renee.

419
00:13:22.719 --> 00:13:23.928
- I'm Jimmy.
- You're Jimmy.

420
00:13:24.012 --> 00:13:25.305
- I am so starstruck.
- It's OK.

421
00:13:25.388 --> 00:13:27.056
- I'm so sorry.
This is weird because--

422
00:13:27.140 --> 00:13:29.434
so. OK. I'm a manager in LA.
so I never get starstruck.

423
00:13:29.517 --> 00:13:31.060
But I--I think that
you are such a talent. and...

424
00:13:31.144 --> 00:13:32.312
- Oh.

425
00:13:32.395 --> 00:13:33.813
- The series meant
so much to me.

426
00:13:33.896 --> 00:13:35.815
- I was so lucky to be
a part of that world.

427
00:13:35.857 --> 00:13:37.483
- Have you ever thought about
doing a rewatch podcast?

428
00:13:37.525 --> 00:13:39.110
You know.
they're really big right now.

429
00:13:39.152 --> 00:13:40.486
where you go through
old episodes and discuss them?

430
00:13:40.528 --> 00:13:41.696
- I don't think enough people

431
00:13:41.779 --> 00:13:42.947
want to hear me talk
about that.

432
00:13:43.031 --> 00:13:44.032
- Girl. shut up!
- Are you kidding?

433
00:13:44.115 --> 00:13:45.033
- We love the show!
- No.

434
00:13:45.116 --> 00:13:46.326
- We've watched it all.

435
00:13:46.409 --> 00:13:47.493
- People would love
that content.

436
00:13:47.577 --> 00:13:49.162
Like. the Hope storyline.
you know?

437
00:13:49.245 --> 00:13:50.955
When did you realize your
daughter was gonna be evil?

438
00:13:51.039 --> 00:13:52.999
Was it from the beginning.
or did it slowly dawn on you?

439
00:13:53.082 --> 00:13:54.792
- Well. her father was
a wicked demigod.

440
00:13:54.876 --> 00:13:56.294
so it kind of
tipped it off for me.

441
00:13:56.377 --> 00:13:57.670
- Right.

442
00:13:57.712 --> 00:13:59.005
Mysteriously impregnated
at a demon ritual?

443
00:13:59.047 --> 00:14:00.173
I was like.
that's gonna come back.

444
00:14:00.214 --> 00:14:01.674
- It did.
- [chuckles] Yeah.

445
00:14:01.716 --> 00:14:03.051
Do you mind if we get a photo?

446
00:14:03.134 --> 00:14:04.552
- Of course.

447
00:14:04.635 --> 00:14:05.970
- I'm sorry. I'm sweating.
I'm--[laughs]

448
00:14:06.054 --> 00:14:07.180
- [chuckling]
- It's OK.

449
00:14:07.221 --> 00:14:08.473
- Yay.
- Ah!

450
00:14:08.556 --> 00:14:09.932
Smile big!
- Yay. Yay.

451
00:14:10.016 --> 00:14:11.684
- Bigger! Ah. cuties!

452
00:14:11.726 --> 00:14:13.186
- Not that big.
Not that big.

453
00:14:13.269 --> 00:14:14.937
- Split the difference.
Split the difference.

454
00:14:15.021 --> 00:14:16.856
- Maybe I should just start
over and get all new fans.

455
00:14:16.939 --> 00:14:18.483
I mean. there are people
born every day. right?

456
00:14:18.566 --> 00:14:19.817
- I gotta tell you. I mean.

457
00:14:19.901 --> 00:14:21.194
as someone who just got
their first fan.

458
00:14:21.277 --> 00:14:22.695
you really need to cherish
these moments.

459
00:14:22.737 --> 00:14:24.113
- It's been 12 minutes.
and I said 10.

460
00:14:24.197 --> 00:14:25.656
- Oh! [scoffs]

461
00:14:25.740 --> 00:14:27.325
- OK. hey. just try
to keep it together.

462
00:14:27.408 --> 00:14:28.659
- [breathing deeply]
- All right?

463
00:14:28.743 --> 00:14:30.286
- No promises.

464
00:14:30.370 --> 00:14:31.496
- OK.

465
00:14:32.538 --> 00:14:34.957
- Hello.
How can I do better for you?

466
00:14:35.041 --> 00:14:38.211
- Oh. no.
I just wanted to say thank you.

467
00:14:38.294 --> 00:14:39.879
- Oh.

468
00:14:39.962 --> 00:14:41.714
You're--you're welcome.
For what?

469
00:14:41.798 --> 00:14:43.716
- Well. my mom and I
have been. like.

470
00:14:43.800 --> 00:14:47.053
huge fans of yours ever since
"Live Free or Diet."

471
00:14:47.095 --> 00:14:50.056
and we came to Vegas.
and we saw you at the Palmetto.

472
00:14:50.139 --> 00:14:51.557
And then we were. like...
[laughing]

473
00:14:51.599 --> 00:14:54.227
Literally quoting your jokes
for 10 hours

474
00:14:54.268 --> 00:14:56.396
the entire car ride home.

475
00:14:56.437 --> 00:14:58.231
It was. like. the best weekend.

476
00:14:58.272 --> 00:15:00.066
- Oh. I'm so glad.
Thank you.

477
00:15:00.149 --> 00:15:04.320
- Anyway. we made you something
to say thank you.

478
00:15:06.447 --> 00:15:08.574
It's you. Barry. and Cara.

479
00:15:08.616 --> 00:15:10.785
[chuckles]
- Wow.

480
00:15:10.868 --> 00:15:12.412
- And we made this
completely out of

481
00:15:12.495 --> 00:15:13.913
natural seeds and grains.

482
00:15:13.996 --> 00:15:15.540
29 types.

483
00:15:15.623 --> 00:15:18.042
- Whew!
- We were sorting yellow peas

484
00:15:18.126 --> 00:15:19.919
for an entire winter
just to nail

485
00:15:20.002 --> 00:15:22.380
your light honey blonde.

486
